	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>San&#45;Francisco</placeName> <date>October the 31st.&#47;1862</date>.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)">My Rev&#58; Friend <addressee>Leeser</addressee>&#33;</p>
				<p>Long has it been my duty to write to you informing you<lb/> of my dear Husband&#44; children and my constant good<lb/> health and happiness hoping the same is with you&#44;<lb/> which is <sic>allway&#39;s</sic> the greatest blessing&#44; I have written<lb/> one letter since I have been here&#44; but received no answer<lb/> no doubt you have never received it&#44; I hope you will<lb/> please me with a letter as it will please me very much.<lb/>  I make good use of the Prayer book and take it to your<lb/> Synagogue&#44; I have often spoken about you to our<lb/> <persName>Rev. E. Hohn</persName> he is a fine man and is liked very<lb/> much&#44; I wish you could see what a nice Synagogue<lb/> we have here&#44; I will send you one of my <sic>card&#39;s</sic> hoping<lb/> you will return the compliment&#44; I can also inform you<lb/> the best of my dear brother <persName>David</persName> and his family&#44; little<lb/> <persName>Moses</persName> will be Ber<add>&#63;</add>it<add>&#63;</add>ag tomorrow&#44; they do not live<lb/> in the City they live in <placeName>San&#45;Jose</placeName> which is 50 miles<lb/> from here&#44; I hope you will excuse me for my poor<lb/> writing as my little boy 11 <sic>month&#39;s</sic> old who wishes to have<lb/> his hand in it&#44; and my oldest a boy 3 &#189; year old</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>I must say myself that they are fine <sic>boy&#39;s</sic>&#44;<lb/> My dear Husband <sic>send&#39;s</sic> his best <sic>regard&#39;s</sic> to you.<lb/>  I hope you will visit Father <sic>occasionaly</sic>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I remain your sincere friend.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Isabella Meyerfeld</persName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">P. S. My dear Sister in law tells me she is<lb/> acquainted with you therefore I need not introduce<lb/> you.  <persName role="author">I. Meyerfeld</persName>.</p>
		</body>
